Project: Play to Heal: An Interactive Maze Game Controlled by Hand Gestures Using MediaPipe and OpenCV for Hand Rehabilitation
Course: AI491-GRADUATION PROJECT (1)
Advisor: Dr. Dana Rashidat

Description:
This file contains the recorded sessions and discussions held with Dr. Dana Rashidat regarding the planning, development, and evaluation of our graduation project. The recordings document:

Guidance on project objectives, research question, and expected outcomes.

Feedback on game design, maze structure, hand gesture integration using MediaPipe and OpenCV.

Discussions on performance analytics, AI-based adaptation, and usability considerations.

Suggestions for alternative testing approaches and validation methods.

Clarifications on project requirements, milestones, and submission expectations.

These recordings serve as a comprehensive reference for the project development process and can be used for review, future evaluation, and to ensure alignment with advisor recommendations.
